jalse.entities

Interface EntityVisitor

  • Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface EntityVisitor
    EntityVisitor allows Entity within an EntityContainer to be walked through one by one recursively. These are walked through breadth-first and their walking can be filtered by suppling different EntityVisitor.EntityVisitResult.

    1. EntityVisitor.EntityVisitResult.CONTINUE the walker will continue as normal.
    2. EntityVisitor.EntityVisitResult.IGNORE_CHILDREN the walker will not walk through any children of this entity.
    3. EntityVisitor.EntityVisitResult.IGNORE_SIBLINGS the walker will ignore all new siblings (only processing the current entity and it's children).
    4. EntityVisitor.EntityVisitResult.EXIT the walker will exit walking and reset.

    Entities can be walked through using Entities.walkEntityTree(EntityContainer, int, EntityVisitor).
    Author:
    Elliot Ford
